items.name: GenshinSplashCharacter-Style
items.description:
I made this LoRA to give generations a dynamic and epic look, reminiscent of the Genshin characters' splash screens!
It works really well with both charachters, character LoRAs and landscapes, if you want to spice up some fantasy setting.

VERSION 2
I retrained the LoRA with upscaled images and revised the trigger words since "splash" gave it a strong bias towards water.
Now the triggerword is "gs2", but the LoRA also works well without the trigger.

The LoRA is now more flexible and easily steered towards the desired result.
Faces are still wonky, but you can fix them with inpainting (or automate the process in Automatic1111 with the extension "after detailer")

You can still use words like "swirling" "dynamic" or similar to give it more dynamism.
-------

VERSION 1
Use its trigger words and a description of the background splash theme to bias it towards different colors or elements, for example you can append to your prompt:
"red_theme", "purple_theme", "magma, fire tornado, red_theme", "ice crystals, blue_theme" etc. and play with the weights of your tags if necessary (refer to the example images).
It is possible that the faces are not so well generated. This is normal since this LoRA focuses on the background. To improve the faces, just inpaint them :D

This LoRA also likes water quite a bit, so if you need, put something like "(water, blue, waves:1.5)" in your negative prompt
-------


The image examples i posted contain:
- simple prompts with character description + color/element theme
- this LoRA mixed with other character/style LoRAs i trained

The samples are generated with the following negative embeddings i found here and there on the internet: bad-artist, bad-hands-5, bad-image-v2-39000, bad_prompt_version2.

If you like this model, consider offering me a coffee! :D https://ko-fi.com/erentil

items.name: srgrafoStyle
items.description:
srgrafoStyle - Preserving Legacy LORA

This is not my work and I don't plan to support this, just trying to preserve this LORA for the community.

Looking forward to seeing what people create with it.

Note On Example Prompts

Model: AnyPastel_HARD

VAE: Anything3, but really any can work

Used Intensity of 1.0 - I don't necessarily think this is best but I wanted to show what this LORA is doing

No cherry picked / clean ups on images, txt-to-image only (With some highrest & control net test for one).. which will show the pain I had with text / signatures (this LORA feels pretty overtrained, be careful with high intensity)

  • I do my best to not overly pollute examples with several LORA / TI's - the goal being to show this LORA off - but you will get a lot of mileage out of easynegative or other similar Anatomy fixing TI's.

  • This does play well with other LORA's but I don't show that off.

Prompting / Info

  • This LORA likes to force characters into specific positions, you can override this by lowering it's intensity or using an aggressive CONTROL NET pose influence.

  • This model really really likes to inject signatures / text when you have it at full strength, especially resolutions outside 512 / 512 - you can kill this by lowering it's intensity / in-painting.

  • I like the aesthetic this brings to images but it does take a bit of getting used to. I use similar terms in a lot of my prompts to get lighting / tones correct.

Acknowledgments / Credits

  • Credit to the original artist SrGrafo

    • I know very little about this artist

  • Original LORA author.. I have no idea - everything around this LORA has been nuked / removed.

items.name: Spooning Position LoRA
items.description:
This is my LoRA for the spooning position. It's a bit volatile, but inpainting the small off-details should do the trick. It is also rather prone to doing anal, and I suspect that this was an oversight in my dataset. Try '(anal)' in your negative prompts to counteract this.

I use 0.75 strength, but it is usable at 0.6-0.8 comfortably. Notably, the testicles are a bit off at times, but this is a failure of generation along the line of hands/feet in which it's more luck dependent. This model doesn't require any specific keywords except general sex or sex adjacent tags. Provided in the keyword section is tags I believe will work in tandem well.

Images generated on my Galena, Euclase, and Sardonyx models. Since these models are based on AOM3, and this LoRA was trained on NovelAI, expect it to work with other anime based models. All images are generated with Hires fix and the Orangemix VAE.

items.name: Style of HOPA Games - landscapes & scenery concept art in style of video games (hoppagames)
items.description:
What can I create with this?

Whatever you want, but here are a few ideas:

  1. Video games concept art (as a reference for the art team)

  2. HQ fantasy landscapes wallpapers

  3. Add backgrounds to your characters by adding "background in the style of hoppagames" (experimental)

Complete workflow

Recommended to have StylePile extension installed and a ChatGTP account.

Positive prompt structure

style of (hoppagames:1.0), (Award-winning photograph), {your subject tags}, {style tags}

Example positive prompt

Replace bold text with your subject descriptors:

style of (hoppagames:1.0), (Award-winning photograph), (Japanese garden), (Autumn foliage), (Vibrant colors), (Fallen leaves), (Nature's beauty), (Red and gold hues), (Maple trees), (Reflections on water), (Peaceful tranquility), (Traditional wooden architecture), (Rustic bridges), (Soothing natural sounds), (Seasonal delight), (Serene garden views), (Low-angle perspective), (natural lighting), (Wide-angle lens capturing scenery), hidden objects games, video game concept art, (8K Unity wallpaper), fine details, award-winning image, highly detailed, 16k, cinematic perspective, ((video game environment concept art style)), pretty colors, cinematic environment

Negative prompt structure

I use Deep Negative and Negative Facelift, plus I add negative tags from the model I am using (take from landscape not people in examples or comments)

Example negative prompt

neg_facelift512, ng_deepnegative_v1_75t, watermark, signature, worst quality, low quality, medium quality, deleted, lowres, comic, (watermarks), watermark, signature

Settings

I used 960x640 px canvas size, without a hi-res fix to generate examples, but feel free to start with a smaller size canvas (768x512) and apply a hi-res fix OR send it to IMG2IMG and upscale with the same prompt and denoising of 0.2-0.5.

CFG scale and steps you can copy from your model examples but should work well on most of the models with CFG of 7-9 and 50-70 steps.

The style is very strong at 1:0 strength so choose a model that is well-responsive to prompting rather than chosen for visual style because it will be overwritten by the style. I found Deliberate to be a well-behaving model for the purpose, but others worked ok as well.

Unique Subject generation workflow

Step 1: ChatGTP

Go to ChatGTP, copy this command, and replace the bold text with your own scene idea and the number of variations you want. I use 3, which should be enough to get you a subject you will like.

describe an award-winning photograph of a wedding shop interior in a maximum of 15 phrases 1-3 words long, put them in brackets and separate brackets by commas in one line. Talk about all the objects in the scene. Use this example for the structure but ignore values: A cozy living room with (Plush comfortable sofa), (fireplace), (Soft fluffy throw pillows), (Warm, cozy blankets), (Rustic, wooden coffee table), (Plush fluffy rug), (Comfy, oversized armchair), (elegant and framed portrait photos on the wall), (Vintage patterned curtains), (Bookshelf with family photo albums and books), (Accent lighting for artwork and photos), (Artisanal and handcrafted pottery and ceramics), (earthy natural wood decor), (a vase with fresh flowers), (wooden side table with a reading lamp). Give me 3 different ideas

Step 2: Feed StylePile

In your positive prompt, replace subject tags with [X] and copy-paste results from ChatGTP into [X] variables field in StylePile part. Remove the "." at the end of each idea because you have "[X]," in your prompt and you don't want it to become "[subject.],"

The positive prompt is now:

style of (hoppagames:1.0), [X], (Low-angle perspective), (natural lighting), (Wide-angle lens capturing scenery), hidden objects games, video game concept art, (8K Unity wallpaper), fine details, award-winning image, highly detailed, 16k, cinematic perspective, ((video game environment concept art style)), pretty colors, cinematic environment

The StylePile's X variables field is now:

(Award-winning photograph), (Japanese garden), (Peaceful pond), (Serene rock formations), (Colorful koi fish), (Zen garden), (Ornamental trees), (Moss-covered stones), (Delicate flowers), (Traditional lanterns), (Stone pathways), (Cherry blossom trees), (Bamboo fences), (Red bridges), (Tranquil ambiance)

(Award-winning photograph), (Japanese garden), (Lush greenery), (Pristine landscaping), (Water features), (Stone statues), (Symmetrical design), (Manicured trees), (Perfectly trimmed shrubs), (Sculpted bushes), (Garden art), (Traditional architecture), (Tea house), (Bonsai trees), (Impeccable precision)

(Award-winning photograph), (Japanese garden), (Autumn foliage), (Vibrant colors), (Fallen leaves), (Nature's beauty), (Red and gold hues), (Maple trees), (Reflections on water), (Peaceful tranquility), (Traditional wooden architecture), (Rustic bridges), (Soothing natural sounds), (Seasonal delight), (Serene garden views)

Step 3 - Generate, Pick & Upscale

Setting batch to 1 will produce 3 images if you have 3 subjects in StylePile. You can do 2 batches, so a total of 6 small images should be enough to pick a winner.

Your winner goes to IMG2IMG and upscales to your desired size with 0.2 denoising.

Enjoy and please share your best results in the comments!

关于图像模糊问题

请使用controlnet进行分块放大修复，如果这还帮不到你你可以借助外援继续放大，电脑不太好的玩家建议使用Topaz和Upscayl进行放大，Upscayl目前是免费的而且速度很快，相关使用教程可以在YOUTUBE和BILIBILI上找到，有很多的视频博主讲解了contronlnet的使用方法，另外图像设置也尽量按照示例图参数不要随意改动，图像采样一般只用DPM++SDE，超级分辨率放大算法请使用4x-UltraSharp，当然其它的算法也可以自行尝试

About image blur

Please use controlnet to zoom in and repair the blocks. If this still doesn’t help you, you can continue to zoom in with the aid of foreign aid. Players with poor computers are recommended to use Topaz and Upscayl for zooming in. Upscayl is currently free and very fast. Related tutorials It can be found on YOUTUBE and BILIBILI. There are many video bloggers explaining how to use contronlnet. In addition, the image settings should also follow the example image parameters as much as possible and do not change at will. Generally, only DPM++SDE is used for image sampling. Super resolution zoom-in algorithm please Use 4x-UltraSharp, of course other algorithms can also be tried by yourself

Project All In One (AIO)

Please Red Description

Important: Having multiple models uploaded here on civitai has made it difficult for me to respond to each and every comment. One of the ways I plan on addressing this is via the creation of a pdf guide for each and every model (think of it as the models documentation). This will take a while though. So in the meantime, if you have any questions or feedback -

visit my thread of the Unstable Diffusion Discord

This model is a merge between all of my previously released models and, some unreleased models.

Going forward, all future models and updates to existing models will also be added/updated on this model.

ChangeLog :

7/31/23 V6

  • Rebuilt from the ground up.

  • Added models : Cine Diffusion, Electric Eden, Based Model, Another Damn Art Model (ADAM), Lomostyle, Doomer Boomer, and an unreleased Anime fine-tune

Recommended Settings

Clipskip: 1

ENSD: 31337

Sampler:

  • DPM++ SDE Karras, 30 - 40 steps

  • DPM++ 2M Karras, 30 - 60 steps

  • Heun, 20 steps, Sigma Churn = 1

  • Euler, 20 - 70 steps, Sigma Churn = 1

These parameters are not strictly required, experiment around with other samplers and parameter values. You might find something that works better for you.

items.name: Mink (Dragon Half)
items.description:
Mink is the main character from Dragon Half.

The main trigger is mink_\(dragon_half\), but it also includes: bikini armor, dragon horns, dragon wings, dragon tail, and knee boots, if you want to mix and match various parts. Additional the LoRA comes with retro artstyle trigger to give Mink the original anime look. Weight 0.8 - 1.0 is recommended.

Activation tags

1) mink_\(dragon_half\) is the main trigger. Technically it shouldn't add anything else, but other tags might still bleed into the image. If that turns out to be the case I recommended either decreasing the weight, or putting other activation tags into the negative prompt. If you decide to lower the weight then I recommend adding red hair and red eyes tags too.
2) dragon horns are a bit hit-or-miss. The official art sometimes portraits Mink as have three pairs of horns, while anime and manga show only a single pair. This tag is used to differentiate between them. I actually suggest putting this tag into a negative prompt, as it looks better in my opinion.
3) bikini armor creates the clothes Mink is usually wearing.
4) dragon wings and dragon tail are self explanatory.
5) knee boots are the golden metal boots Mink is wearing along with her outfit.

Bonus tags:
a) retro artstyle forces the anime aesthetics.
b) illustration and official art can be used to shift the art style toward the official illustrations.

Misc.

Be warned, easynegative doesn't gel well with Mink's eyes.

1.0 is obsolete and shouldn't be used, but I'm keeping it as it can produce some interesting results with unique art style.

Trained on 89 images (x5 repeats), with person used as a class. 8 epochs, 64 DIM / 32 Alpha. Base model used for training was animefull_final, but the example images were created on AbyssOrangeMix.

My first attempt at making a LoRA. Feedback is welcome.

items.description:
[Note: LyCORIS version is now available here]

Trained on official art from the game and artist this LoRA was blessed by RNGJesus to reliably output some really high quality artwork. It works both as a style for the game and as a general one.

How to use
Just prompt (1boy) or (1girl) and then fantasy tags like "armor", "pointy ears" and so on to trigger the style. You can further refined it using fantasy type characters tags from the Etrian Odyssey game. See the sample images for prompts. I also uploaded the training tags as a separate file you can use as a template to modify.

AUTOMATIC1111 users can utilize the wildcard prompt below to randomly prompt classes and races from the game.. I recommend using "3d" and "realistic" in negatives on AOM2 and other models with mixed in realism. "Chibi" also seems to work fine for more chubby little adventurers.

<lora:EtrianV2:1>
({full|upper} body)
(solo)
(1girl)(facing viewer)
({human|elf|bunny_ear|goat_horns|horse_ears|cat_ears|demon|angel} girl)
in ({barbarian|bard|cleric|druid|fighter|monk|paladin|ranger|rogue|sorcerer|warlock|wizard|artificer} outfit)

Don't forget to review and upload your own images, it's always fun to see what you're creating!

After 9 years in development, hopefully it will have been worth the weight!

This is a lora file trained on 91 handpicked fempyro images. There are no 3d/sfm images included, exclusively digital art.
